This paper deals with improving knowledge graph embeddings using machine learning techniques, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for link prediction, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as feature reshaping and circular convolution, which are commonly used in NLP tasks (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a subfield of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques such as link prediction, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR).
